Tan (1989) did not mention Dicranoloma brachypelma, so Dicranoloma brevisetum sec. Tan 1989 can be congruent with either Dicranoloma brevisetum sec,.Tan & Koponen 1983 or Dicranum braunii sec. Norris & Koponen 1990, but not with both.

Eddy (1988) specifically mentioned forms of Dicranoloma assimile that look similar to Dicranoloma rugifolium.

incl. forms with rugose leaves that Norris and Koponen place in Dicranum rugifolium.
Tan & Koponen (1983) recognised Dicranoloma brachypelma. The type of Leucoloma brachypelma is from Java, so was not in Norris & Koponen's (1990) treatment, which is for New Guinea.
incl. Dicranoloma havilandii; excl. Dicranoloma perarmatum
both misidentified type of Dicranoloma defoliatum
Both treatments misidentified the type of Dicranoloma defoliatum; Tan (1989) recognises Dicranoloma braunfelsioides, which Eddy (1988) does not mention.
Eddy (1988) did not include Dicranoloma euryloma var. rugifolium in his synonymy, but mentions forms of Dicranoloma assimile that look like the type of Dicranoloma euryloma var. rugifolium.
both misidentified type of Dicranoloma defoliatum
